column1: Historical and projected real gross domestic product (GDP) and growth rates of GDP for baseline countries/regions (in billions of 2015 dollars) 1970-2033

Note: High income countries/1, High income countries less USA/2, Upper-middle income countries/3, Lower-middle income countries/4, and Low income countries/5 are categorized according to the World Bank country classifications by income level.

BRIICs/6 are Brazil, Russia, India, Indonesia, China; Former centrally planned economies/7 Cyprus, Malta, Recently acceded countries, Other Central Europe, Former Soviet Union; USMCA/8 are Canada, Mexico, United States; Europe and Central Asia/9 are Europe, Former Soviet Union.

Middle East and North Africa/10 are Middle East and North Africa; Other Southeast Asia Outlook/11 are Malaysia, Philippines, Thailand, Vietnam; and Other South America Outlook/12 Chile, Colombia, Peru, Bolivia, Paraguay, Uruguay.

Source: World Bank World Development Indicators, IHS Global Insight, Oxford Economics Forecasting, as well as estimated and projected values developed by the Economic Research Service all converted to a 2015 base year.
Contact: Wendy Zeng and William Johnson, USDA, Economic Research Service, Market and Trade Economics Division, International Trade Branch.
Real 2015 GDP levels (billions USD) (prefix y-) and annual growth rates (right side of table, prefix g-).
